trend_summary: Across the image sequence, low-rise residential fabric thickens, commercial strips widen along the highway spine, and several wooded tracts convert to cul-de-sac housing. Minor greening projects appear in park blocks, but impervious cover slowly expands, especially near the central interchange. Overall, suburban sprawl with steady infill, not high-rise urbanisation, dominates the period.
notable_changes: Progressive replacement of forest patches in the south-west by curved-street subdivisions.
Enlargement of the cloverleaf/diamond highway interchange and adjacent service lanes.
Increase in big-box roofs and parking lots on the eastern commercial corridor.
New neighborhood park and athletic fields add greenery in the north-central section.
General rise in roof density within older subdivisions through lot-splitting and extensions.
